	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2025-02-21T17:33:03">20 Microns Limited is an India-based company, which is engaged in business of manufacturing and selling of industrial micronized minerals and specialty chemicals. The Company manufactures and supplies a wide range of micronized minerals, white minerals, and specialty chemicals to both local and international markets. Its product portfolio includes industrial minerals, and specialty chemical. Its industrial minerals include ball clay, barytes, bentonite, bleaching earth, calcined kaolin, calcium carbonate, diatomaceous earth, dolomite, feldspar, fullers earth, kaolin, mica, perlite, ramming mass, silica, talc, wollastonite, and others. Its specialty chemical includes activators-magnesium oxide, activators-zinc oxide, desiccants, flame retardants &amp; smoke suppressant, fumed silica, mullite, organo clays-rheological additive, performance mineral additive, precipitated silica, rheology modifier, semi reinforcing eco green filler, synthetic barytes, synthetic barytes, and others.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2025-11-12T02:31:48"> BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 September 2025, 20 Microns Ltd revenues increased 2% to RS4.78B. Net income applicable to common stockholders decreased less than 1% to RS342.5M. Revenues reflect Micronized Minerals segment increase of 99% to RS4.81B. Net income reflects Litigation Settlement Expenses decrease of 80% to RS330K (expense), Other Income increase of 1% to RS26.3M (income).</Text>
	</TextInfo>
